ally looked down, and made fun of, intelligent kids. It was somehow &quot;uncool&quot; to be smart, or to try to do well. In the private school where friends, and family of mine, went the smart students were honored and looked up to. The contrast was night from day. I can't say all public education is bad or that all private education is good but public education has declined so far I don't believe it can be saved. So many others posters have made articulate comments about what is wrong with the public education system that I won't waste anymore time on the subject. All that is left to say is the writer is either a complete idiot or has some ulterior motive. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="964" language="en" documentId="3090" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="waxwell" date="Aug 29, 2013 7:45PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="7" thumbsDown="0" origId="3090" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="964"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>